In this video I refer to a colleague who recently took his life. He was also a first responder like I was. I don’t know him very well but honestly it stirred up a lot of emotion for me the last few days. I’ve come a long way managing Complex PTSI,MDD,ADHD, and Anxiety. All manifesting itself after a 16 year career as a firefighter EMT. I was fortunate enough to ask for and accept help. This college wasn’t the first to take his life. There are others I was closer too and it hurts to think this is still an option for people. I’ve been there too and somehow pulled through knowing the light would come back. Eventually. I’m not cured or anything. Far from it. It’s a constant battle and this is the first year I’m recognizing significant improvement. I stay busy with Yoga, weightlifting, and Pickleball!! (My new favorite lol). 
——
If anyone out there is struggling and doesn’t know where to start, I’m happy to try and guide you into the next step. Just know, it doesn’t last forever and there are WAY more options than I had ever imagined out there. You just need to find what works for you and keep trying. ❤️✌️🙏🏾
.

DO NOT TOP YOUR TREES! “Topping” refers to cutting any limb or main stem at random. Especially when you cut a main leader of a tree to reduce its height. It’s extremely frustrating to see trees being “professionally” cut like this. This wasn’t the only tree either. I was working in a residential “community” where services like landscaping are provided. Many of the trees were randomly lopped off to improve the view.  Funny thing is that the stress branches, called Water Sprouts, will grow back thicker, faster, and HIGHER than the tree would have normally grown. Plus it looks ugly and will never recover from such a butchering 🔪 . Too bad for these residents. I guess you get what you pay for! - In follow up to realizing this, I’ve reached out to the community board to explain the severity of the situation. Not to place blame but to educate. Likely, the persons who “pruned” these trees literally had no idea and were taking advantage of an opportunity to make some easy $$. 
.
Thoughts out there?? 
.
